  "riddle": "1. Unearth the path of a Breton deputy — whose constituency claims a voice in the National Assembly?\n\n2. In representation, how many members of parliament does this district send to the grand assembly?\n\n3. What year did two scholars propose a contemporary view of a cultural identity that binds a vast region?\n\n4. Seek the height at which this cultural umbrella stands, from the ground up — what is its elevation in meters?\n\n5. Close by, count how many hospitals serve the community surrounding this cultural identity.\n\n6. Before moving on, find the absolute difference between the elevation and the number of hospitals you just discovered.\n\n7. Now, what is the altitude above sea level at the site where relations between France and Africa unfold?\n\n8. A pivotal moment in national governance — what was the latest presidential election referenced in this article?\n\n9. Investigate the elevation of the scene set by the last French presidential election — how high does it rise?\n\n10. Nearby, how many places of worship can be found in proximity to the site of the recent election?\n\n11. Take the absolute difference between the elevation of the 2022 election and the count of churches nearby.\n\n12. Turning to the north, what is the population count of the expansive nation that is Canada?\n\n13. Within the pages of justice, how many languages are spoken in the judiciary of this country?\n\n14. Consider the essence of the count from the previous clue — what is the sum of its distinct prime factors?\n\n15. Reflect on your timeline, how many days span from the start of 1996 until a day in March 2026?\n\n16. Now for a twist, find the digital root of the total days calculated — what single digit does it collapse into?\n\n17. To conclude this journey, compute the digital root of the sum (of clues 5, 6, and 16) — what single digit emerges from your journey?",
